                    "description": "Final Project for a Residential pedestrian neighborhood  \n+Final project has been completed with residential buildings of five floors for the whole site building area, 4.5 hectares, to be developed in two steps, the total number of flats is 284 with a population of 1280 residents.The site structure proposed on the first version has been preserved. Pedestrian neighbourhood, building\u2019s orientation as to receive maximum sunlight in winter and lower in summer, reducing impact of winter cold winds , using solar energy, with parking only on the perimeter of the area ,with all   services located in a central pedestrian spine, preserving existing forests alongside the river . Project Value Euro 24 millions\n\n+A second more detailed project was prepared for the part of the site which is still empty, covering an area of 28.000 sq.mt., the proposed development is based on the same principles as those defining the first project, the total number of residential units for this project is 218.\n\n+First version of the plan for the rehabilitation and reuse of an industrial area, 52.000sq.mt. in the northern part of the town of Chiguayante in the Region of Bio-Bio. The area where the industry has been located from 1968 which used to be outside the town is today surrounded by residential development on three sides and the river Bio-Bio on its eastern border. The proposed residential neighbourhood will preserve the existing forest alongside the river, reuse the industrial building as a commercial-recreation center, reuse the water of the existing well for gardens and green areas, and design a pedestrian development for 390 residential units in different blocks using renewable energy for the buildings.",
